To program a large problem, the solution is to break it up into smaller manageable tasks. write method for each task.
A method is a grouping of lines of code that perform a task. 
Some methods return value and some don't.
Some methods receive input and some don't.

Method Header

public static void main (String [] args){
    // call method
    // double y = findSquare(9);
    // 
    // or system.out.print(method(parameter))

    double num = 3.4;
    System.out.print("num is" + num); // this is 3.4 
    callByValue(num);
    System.out.print("num is" + num); // 3.4
}


public static double findSquare(int x) {
    return Math.pow(x, 2.0);
}


public static void callByValue(double x){
    // change x 
    x = 68.01
    System.out.println("x value in the method is: " + x);  // 68.01
    // when you pass a value or parameter into a method, the change in value of that parameter is not permanent so it stays the same as before. (3.4 before and 3.4 after ... not 68.01) PASS BY VALUE
    // PASS BY REFERENCE - instead of sending a copy of the parameter, you send the address of the parameter 
}  